\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Exceptions
\series default
:
 Exceptions to any requirement of this policy shall be documented in writing with a business justification and approved by the IT Director in accordance with the exception management framework established in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 Exceptions affecting CJIS vendor compliance assessment cadences,
 CJIS Security Addendum verification requirements,
 or the exercise of contractual audit rights for vendors with access to CJI shall require County Manager approval in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.08"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Delegation of Authority and Decision Rights).
 No exception shall be granted on an open-ended basis;
 each exception shall specify a defined remediation timeline.
 No exception shall be granted that would place County systems or CJI out of compliance with applicable CJIS Security Policy obligations.
